"Abstract. We provide unconditional results and conditional ones under the assumption of GRH (Generalized Riemann Hypothesis) on the distribution of quadratic residues and quadratic non-residues in ℤ/Nℤ$\\mathbb {Z}/N\\mathbb {Z}$ , where N=pq$N= pq$ is an RSA modulus used in the Goldwasser–Micali cryptosystem. The paper also discusses cryptographic implications of the results obtained."
